               <msContents>
                  <summary>Missal, መጽሐፈ፡ ቅዳሴ: Ordinary of the Mass. In a gold case, with a plaque on the front that says, ንጉሠ ነ[ገሥት] ኃይለ ሥላሴ.
                    F<locus target="#45r">fols. 45r, </locus>-62r: Anaphora of the Apostles, Qǝddase Ḫawaryat, ቅዳሴ፡ ሐዋርያት፡. F<locus target="#62r">62r, </locus>-68r: Anaphora of Our Lord, ቅዳሴ፡ እግዚእ፡. See Mercer. F<locus target="#68v">68v, </locus>-79v: Anaphora of John, Son of Thunder, Qǝddase Yoḥannǝs Wäldä Nägwädǝgwad, ቅዳሴ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ ወልደ፡ ነጐድጓድ፡. F<locus target="#80r">80r, </locus>-93r: Anaphora of Our Lady Mary attributed to Cyriacus of Bǝhǝnsa, Qǝddase Maryam Gwäs’a, ቅዳሴ፡ ማርያም፡. F<locus target="#93r">93r, </locus>-103v: Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers, Qǝddase za-Śäläsǝtu, ቅዳሴ፡ ዘሠለስቱ፡ ምዕት፡. F<locus target="#104r">104r, </locus>-116r: Anaphora of Athanasius the Apostolic, Qǝddase Atǝnatewos, ቅዳሴ፡ አትናቴዎስ፡. F<locus target="#116v">116v, </locus>-126v: Anaphora of Basil of Caesarea, Qǝddase Baslǝyos, ቅዳሴ፡ ባስልዮስ፡. F<locus target="#127r">127r, </locus>-135v: Anaphora of Gregory, brother of Basil, Qǝddase Gorǝgorǝyos, ‘Ǝḫǝwä Baslǝyos., ቅዳሴ፡ ጎርጎርዮስ፡ እኅወ፡ ባስልዮስ፡. F<locus target="#135v">135v, </locus>-144r: Anaphora of Epiphanius, Qǝddase Epifanǝyos, ቅዳሴ፡ ኤጲፋንዮስ. F<locus target="#144v">144v, </locus>-152r: Anaphora of John Chrysostom, Qǝddase Yoḥannǝs Afä Wärq, ቅዳሴ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ አፈወርቅ፡. F<locus target="#152r">152r, </locus>-160v: Anaphora of Cyril of Alexandria, Qǝddase Qerǝlos, ቅዳሴ፡ ቄርሎስ፡. F<locus target="#161r">161r, </locus>-169r: Anaphora of Jacob of Serugh, Qǝddase Ya’ǝkob Zä-Śǝrug, ቅዳሴ፡ ያዕቆብ፡ ዘሥሩግ፡. F<locus target="#169v">169v, </locus>-176r: Anaphora of Dioscorus, Qǝddase Diosǝqoros, ቅዳሴ፡ ዲዮስቆሮስ፡. F<locus target="#177">177, </locus>-182r: Anaphora of Gregory Nazanzia, ጎርጎርዮስ: ዘእንዚናዙ:, here called "the second Gregory." Sometimes called Anaphora of Gregory of Armenia, the Wonder Worker, ጎርጎርዮስ፡ ዘአርማንያ፡. Notes.  <locus target="#24r">24r, </locus> (and passim) mentions Abba ዮሐንስ (XIX, 192801942) and Abba ቄርሎስ (VI, 1929-1950). <locus target="#24v">24v, </locus> (and passim) mentions "our King," ኃይለ ሥላሴ (1930-1974). <locus target="#44r">44r, </locus>: a concluding note that indicates that "If a priest or a deacon does not participate in the midnight mass, they cannot participate in Holy Communion.  If they break this rule, they will be out of order." <locus target="#182r">182r, </locus>: Colophon: This book was produced by the order of Haile Selassie in 1922 EC in the time of Qerelos (VI). A list of the Echegge and five regional bishops is also given. The head of the Ministry of Pen (ጸሐፌ ትእዛዝ) is ወልደ መስቀል. The scribe is የሽዋ ወርቅ. <locus target="#182v">182v</locus>: a secondary note of memorial to ንቡረ እድ ገብረ መስቀል.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ‘ǝz</textLang>

                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                     <locus target="#182r">Fol. 182r</locus>
                     <q>This book was produced by the order of Haile Selassie in 1922 EC in the time of Qerelos (VI)<gap reason="omitted"/></q>
                     <note>A list of the Echegge and five regional bishops is also given. The head of the Ministry of Pen (ጸሐፌ ትእዛዝ) is ወልደ መስቀል. The scribe is የሽዋ ወርቅ</note>
                     </colophon>

                  </msItem>
